I've now seen all the new hymns sung at least once in my dataset. It looks like <hymn>Softly and Tenderly Jesus Is Calling (#1020)</hymn> is currently the most popular of the new hymns. It's followed by <hymn>This Little Light of Mine (#1028)<hymn> and then <hymn>I Know That the Savior Loves Me (1021)</hymn>, but we'll likely see this change a little bit over the next few weeks and months. 

(For a complete version of this table that includes all hymns, see [here](/overview.qmd).)

## What hymns are most popular each week?

The plot below is not too informative yet because it has only been a month and the overall number of wards singing the new hymns is not high. But we can start to get an idea of what hymns were popular when *of the wards that sang them*. 



::: {.cell .column-page}
::: {.cell-output-display}
![](index_files/figure-html/unnamed-chunk-11-1.png){width=1248}
:::
:::



I'm a little surprised that there aren't too many clear patterns. It might be a sample size issue: less data means proportional data like this is more erratic. But, a few hymns seem to be steadily increasing in popularity. But, we'll have to wait for more time to pass and more wards to sing these hymns before we can say much for sure.


## When during meetings are these hymns sung?

We can now see when during sacrament meetings these hymns have been sung. Again, since I have not seen very many wards singing from this third batch quite yet, it's difficult to notice any patterns. So this is just a very preliminary look based on just a little bit of data. It is noteworthy though that none have been sung as sacrament hymns.



